this whole video is relatively underrated, but i think a particular aspect that not a lot of people think about is how that's a real guitar that he's deftly using as a prop. not a fake cardboard or plastic or whatever else guitar, but a real one with difficult weight to maneuver. learning and getting used to that while practicing such physically demanding and insanely detailed choreo with all sorts of other props and stunts must've been difficult as hell. that's why i try to watch this as much as i can to show my appreciation

From it's storyline, concept, the entirety of the choreography and how Yeonjun delivered it all. Everything about this performance is just perfect. Yeonjun's moves and how he's able to control his body, how precise and spot on he is, and his facial expressions that adds to the perfection of the whole thing, also his really strong stage presense. Remember that doing Str3am is a difficult task, if you are going to do it, please remember to stay healthy, *health first.* okay?okay.(I added this just now because I didn't realize I hadn't put it before, my mistake.). Making v!s!ts increase is not toxic/obsessive behavior as such, it is simply wanting to boost the fame of the artists we like.* Do you think that BTS would be what they are today if ARMY had not left their soul by uploading the views of their videos and making them viral? Choi Yeonjun born September 13, 1999 is the eldest of the group Tomorrow X Together formed under Bighit Music, the same label as BTS. He is the Bighit Legendary Trainee who topped rapping, singing and dancing evaluations in Bighit when he was still a trainee. He has the title 4th Gen It Boy for debuting as a model, actor (cameo), singer, dancer, rapper, composer, lyricist and designer.
